Security Council Postpones Consultation on Iraq 's Letter
UNITED NATIONS , November 14 ( Xinhua ) -- The United Nations Security Council was scheduled to meet on Iraq 's letter on 3 : 30 pm EST Saturday Afternoon , but now it had postponed the meeting to 5 : 00 pm EST , U.N. spokesman 's office announced .
Council sources said the postponement was made at the request of some members of the Security Council .
They said they needed more time for consideration of Iraq 's letter to U.N. chief Kofi Annan which was delivered by Iraq 's Ambassador to the United Nations this morning .
Iraq 's Deputy Prime Minister Tareq Aziz wrote to Annan that Baghdad had decided to rescind its decisions of August 5 and October 31 and resume full and complete cooperation with all U.N. arms inspectors .
The Council will discuss the letter and take its action this afternoon .
